So I always used to use a regular comb for detangling my hair — and every single time, I ended up with so much hair fall and breakage.

Why? Because I usually dry comb my curls after 7 to 10 days — and that’s a tangle disaster!

But the day I switched to a proper detangling comb, I noticed a visible difference in hair breakage.

Switch to a detangling comb that actually cares for your hair!
It’s gentle on knots, perfect for wet or curly hair, and totally ouch-free.

Another charcoal art piece. 🎨

Lately, I haven’t felt like creating content — even though I’ve been consistently doing it since 2019, barely taking any breaks. Things have changed a lot on Instagram. It’s a constant cycle of chasing trends, brainstorming ideas, and planning shoots, Despite negative comments from agencies, brands, and even strangers — stay positive and keep pushing yourself forward.

But one thing I’ve truly realised this year is how many new skills I’ve picked up along the way — reading books for creative inspiration, improving my editing, understanding camera angles, learning negotiation… all while never really pausing. 

Still, my heart feels calm when I sit down to explore charcoal art. I’m loving this new creative space and want to get better at it. 🖤
I really hope you all enjoy this piece. Your comments and support mean the world to me — every word feels like a little push to keep going.

#charcoalart #contentcreator #curlyhairgirl #happinessinart #itsme

Foot Peeling and Exfoliating Foot Mask

😍😍Hit the follow button and comments for the link 

* Peels off dead, dry and calloused skin.
* De-tans feet and fights foot odor.
* Reveals new soft feet in 8-10 days.
* Restores softness to rough feet.

Precautions 
* Before using read the directions and follow them carefully
* Remove nail polish before using.
* Do not use if you have open sores. cuts, and other abrasions on your feet.
* The product should be used immediately after opening.
* The mask is a single-use application; do not reuse.
* We recommend having feet on the ground during treatment.
* Do not forcibly remove dead skin from your feet, let it peel naturally.
* We do not recommend this product if you have abnormally high glucose levels in the blood or are pregnant.
* This product is exclusively for use on feet.
* Do a patch test if you feel that you have sensitive skin.
* Store in a cool dry place. Keep out of reach of children.

Propaganda I’m Not Falling For:
1. Frizz is bad.” — No, it’s texture with a personality.
2. You need to brush your curls daily.” — And start a war with my hair? No thanks.
3. Curly hair isn’t professional.” — My resume says otherwise.
4. Oil solves everything.” — My curls want moisture, not a deep fry.
5. Straightening once won’t hurt.” — And one lie doesn’t break trust, right?
6. Natural curls are low effort.” — Sis, this is a full-time job.
7. DIY masks are always better.” — Not putting fruit salad on my scalp again.

#curlyhair #curlyhairgirls #curlyhairmyths

This simple drink hydrates skin, boosts collagen, fights acne, reduces inflammation, and promotes a natural glow. It also improves digestion and detoxifies the body.

🥄 Recipe:
	•	1 glass water
	•	1 tbsp chia seeds (soaked 10–15 min)
	•	Juice of ½ lemon
	•	A pinch of pink salt
Mix well and drink!

⚠️ Precautions:
	•	Limit to 1 glass/day
	•	Start slow if you’re new to chia or lemon
